The recently discovered Vietnamese crocodile lizard is already vulnerable to smuggling, while the critically endangered Delacour's langurs take refuge in a nature reserve. In springtime, an astonishing diversity of butterfly species congregates in the forest.

programme.title: Wild Vietnam
programme.desc: Travel to southern Vietnam's tropical habitats, home to gibbons and playful macaques, green sea turtles, and Asian black bears. Reintroduced Siamese crocodiles roam the Bau Sau wetlands. The vast Mekong Delta boasts small-clawed otters and thousands of migrating birds, from openbill storks to Oriental darters.

programme.title: Wild Chile
programme.desc: From the cold waters of Tierra Del Fuego and the Antarctic Peninsula to the frozen Patagonian steppe, we follow the animals living there. .

programme.title: Wild Chile
programme.desc: In the South, strong westerlies bring rains that create rich green Valdivian forests, carpeting the neotropic ecozone. .

programme.title: Wild Chile
programme.desc: At its Northern edge, in the Atacama desert, wildlife has spent millions of years adapting to a life without water. .

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol
programme.desc: Everything feels connected as the vets see patterns emerge in their cases. Treating back-to-back Australian Shepherds, waves of animals suffering respiratory ailments, and a rush of lumps and bumps keeps the team hustling. Although the symptoms, breeds, and names can feel alike, no two cases are really the same. .

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol
programme.desc: A major storm blows into Central Michigan, and as the snow piles up, so do the cases! While clients brave the weather to get care for their animals, Dr. Pol and Charles battle thundersnow when responding to an emergency farm call. Dr. Lisa needs ten stitches to repair a horses deep cut, and Dr. Brenda treats a Rottweilers very swollen face. .

programme.title: Pythonathon
programme.desc: PYTHONATHON will chronicle the Florida Fish & Wildlife Conservation Commission's (FWC) latest effort to control the exploding Burmese python populations - a 4 week long hunting season on the invasive snakes with cash prizes to the hunters who bring in the largest and the most snakes - by following hunting teams as they try to stop the invasion and win cash prizes.

programme.title: Reptile Planet
programme.desc: Skittering, swimming and even gliding, over 12,000 species of reptiles roam the world. Crocs, turtles, snakes and lizards have ancestors as old as the dinosaurs and evolution as their friend. These cold-blooded creatures have adapted in clever and lethal ways, from armoured skin and poisonous venom to record-breaking bite force and even blood squirting eyes. This is Reptile Planet!.
